main event: An unidentified object was observed near Cape Canaveral, Florida shortly after a missile launch.
interesting points: The object had a circular shape and was approximately the same magnitude as Venus or Echo I.
The object was white in color and made no sound.
The observer was watching a gas cloud associated with a missile launch when the object was spotted.
The object's flight path included slowing down when reaching the observer's location and Cape Canaveral, and then fading in intensity as it disappeared.
The sighting lasted for 3-4 minutes and was observed by multiple witnesses, including military personnel.
witnesses: a Sandia Corporation engineer and military personnel
